{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865210432,"sessionID":"ses_28631db06ffe42dcYOqg2DSQPy","part":{"id":"prt_d79ce55ab001P9oZGMD4dWynkL","messageID":"msg_d79ce25fc001onQiVXhbCFI9WV","sessionID":"ses_28631db06ffe42dcYOqg2DSQPy","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"toolu_tool-4d7b48b1b8244cbd93bd8802ef8f4554","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project to understand:\n1. The overall project structure (especially the root directory and any docs/planning folders)\n2. The pkg/agentd module - what files exist, what's the architecture\n3. Any existing tasks.md files or similar checklists to understand the format\n4. Any design documents or specs related to AR-018 or idle cleanup\n5. What \"Stage ST-3\" might refer to in terms of design stages\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of the project structure, the agentd module contents, any relevant design patterns or existing task checklists format.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28631a9bdffeHxrfJb06KOgKcw (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Let me provide a detailed summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Summary of the Agentcube Project\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThe project is **AgentCube** - a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents. It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic through session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n**Root Directory Structure:**\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/\nтФЬтФАтФА go.mod                          # Go module: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\nтФЬтФАтФА design.md                       # AR-018 design document (root-level)\nтФЬтФАтФА project.md                      # Project overview document\nтФЬтФАтФА delta-spec.md                   # Delta spec document\nтФЬтФАтФА proposal.md                     # Proposal document\nтФЬтФАтФА test_spec.md                    # Test spec\nтФЬтФАтФА coverage.out                    # Test coverage output\nтФЬтФАтФА .sdd_prompt.md                  # Prompt file with AR-018 specs\nтФЬтФАтФА changes/                        # Change Request directories (AR-001 to AR-018)\nтФВ   тФЬтФАтФА AR-001/                     # Each AR folder contains: tasks.md, design.md, spec.md, proposal.md, delta-spec.md\nтФВ   тФЬтФАтФА AR-002/\nтФВ   тФЬтФАтФА ...\nтФВ   тФФтФАтФА AR-018/                     # Current AR for Agentd Idle Cleanup\nтФЬтФАтФА pkg/                            # Main source code packages\nтФВ   тФЬтФАтФА apis/runtime/v1alpha1/      # Kubernetes CRD types (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\nтФВ   тФЬтФАтФА common/types/               # Common types (SandboxInfo, etc.)\nтФВ   тФЬтФАтФА picod/                      # PicoD daemon (sandbox pod component)\nтФВ   тФЬтФАтФА router/                     # Router component (JWT, session management, reverse proxy)\nтФВ   тФЬтФАтФА store/                      # Redis/Valkey session store\nтФВ   тФФтФАтФА workloadmanager/            # Workload Manager component (GC, lifecycle, handlers)\nтФЬтФАтФА idle-cleanup/                   # Idle cleanup design/spec docs\nтФЬтФАтФА session-routing/                # Session routing design/spec docs\nтФЬтФАтФА python-sdk/                     # Python SDK design/spec docs\nтФЬтФАтФА code-execution/                 # Code execution design/spec docs\nтФЬтФАтФА ci-cd/                          # CI/CD design/spec docs\n```\n\n**Key packages currently exist:**\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` - Kubernetes CRD types\n- `pkg/common/types/` - SandboxInfo and common types\n- `pkg/picod/` - Sandbox pod daemon (10 files)\n- `pkg/router/` - Router HTTP server (14 files)\n- `pkg/store/` - Session store (6 files)\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/` - Workload Manager (22 files + subdirs)\n\n**Note: `pkg/agentd/` does NOT currently exist** - this is the module to be created for AR-018.\n\n---\n\n### 2. The pkg/agentd Module - What Needs to Be Created\n\nThe `pkg/agentd` module is **not yet implemented**. According to the AR-018 delta-spec, the following files need to be created:\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `pkg/agentd/doc.go` | Create | Package documentation |\n| `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` | Create | `IdleCleanupController`, constructor, Start, Stop, runLoop, runOnce, SetIdleTimeout, GetIdleTimeout, GetStats |\n| `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for idle cleanup controller |\n| `pkg/agentd/defaults.go` | Create | `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval` (1 minute), `DefaultIdleTimeout` (15 minutes) constants |\n\n**Architecture from the design.md:**\n```\npkg/agentd/\nтФЬтФАтФА controller/\nтФВ   тФЬтФАтФА idle_cleanup_controller.go    # Main controller implementation\nтФВ   тФЬтФАтФА idle_cleanup_controller_test.go\nтФВ   тФФтФАтФА metrics.go                     # Prometheus metrics\nтФЬтФАтФА config/\nтФВ   тФФтФАтФА cleanup_config.go              # Configuration types\nтФФтФАтФА cleanup/\n    тФЬтФАтФА detector.go                    # Idle detection logic\n    тФЬтФАтФА detector_test.go\n    тФЬтФАтФА cleaner.go                     # Cleanup execution logic\n    тФФтФАтФА cleaner_test.go\n```\n\nHowever, the delta-spec suggests a simpler structure with just:\n- `doc.go`\n- `idle_cleanup.go`\n- `idle_cleanup_test.go`\n- `defaults.go`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing Tasks.md Format\n\nThe `tasks.md` files follow a consistent structure:\n\n**Header Section:**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX тАФ [Title] Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-XXX тАФ [Title] |\n| Module | `pkg/[module]` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S/M/L |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n```\n\n**Task Phases Structure:**\n```markdown\n### Phase 1: [Phase Title] (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: [Task description]\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/[module] -run TestXXX -v`\n\n- [ ] **T1.2**: [Task description]\n  - File: `pkg/[module]/file.go:line-range`\n  - Issue: [Description]\n  - Fix: [Description]\n```\n\n**Additional Sections:**\n- Task Dependencies (ASCII diagram)\n- Verification Commands table\n- Acceptance Criteria (checkboxes)\n- Files Modified/Created table\n- Notes section\n- Implementation Timeline table\n\n---\n\n### 4. AR-018 and Idle Cleanup Design Documents\n\n**AR-018 Location:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-018/`\n\n**AR-018 Files:**\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `tasks.md` | Task checklist (currently placeholder - needs to be filled) |\n| `design.md` | Technical design (currently placeholder - needs to be filled) |\n| `spec.md` | Requirements specification (currently placeholder) |\n| `proposal.md` | Proposal document |\n| `delta-spec.md` | Detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios - **THIS IS THE MOST COMPLETE DOCUMENT** |\n\n**Related idle-cleanup docs:**\n- `idle-cleanup/design.md` - Controller-runtime based design (uses Sandbox CR watching)\n- `idle-cleanup/spec.md` - Idle cleanup specification\n\n**Key AR-018 delta-spec highlights:**\n\nThe `IdleCleanupController` should:\n1. **Struct fields**: store, lifecycleManager, interval, idleTimeout, stopCh, wg, logger\n2. **Default constants**: `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval = 1 * time.Minute`, `DefaultIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n3. **Methods**: Start, Stop, runLoop, runOnce, SetIdleTimeout, GetIdleTimeout, GetStats\n4. **Behavior**: \n   - Lists sessions from Store\n   - Checks `LastActivity` timestamp\n   - Skips sessions with zero LastActivity\n   - Deletes idle sessions via `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox`\n   - Handles NotFound errors silently\n   - Logs cleanup actions with `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Stage ST-3 Meaning\n\n**Stage ST-3** refers to a design completion stage in the project's development process. Based on the tasks.md files:\n\n- **ST-1**: Core Types & Configuration phase\n- **ST-2**: Store/Interface Implementation phase\n- **ST-3**: Main Lifecycle Methods / Core Logic phase\n- **ST-4** through **ST-N**: Additional phases (handlers, middleware, tests, etc.)\n\nThe pattern from AR-007, AR-008 shows:\n```\nPhase 1: Core Types & Configuration (ST-1)\nPhase 2: Store Implementation (ST-2)\nPhase 3: Kubernetes Client / Lifecycle Methods (ST-3)\nPhase 4: Lifecycle Manager (ST-4)\nPhase 5: Garbage Collector (ST-5)\n...\n```\n\nWhen tasks.md says **\"Design | [Stage ST-3 completed]\"**, it means the design phase has been completed and the task breakdown is ready for implementation. The actual implementation phases are numbered ST-1, ST-2, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Design Patterns from pkg/workloadmanager\n\nThe `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` provides an excellent **reference implementation pattern** for the AR-018 idle cleanup controller:\n\n**Key Patterns:**\n\n1. **Struct with sync.RWMutex for thread-safe fields:**\n```go\ntype GarbageCollector struct {\n    manager     *SandboxLifecycleManager\n    interval    time.Duration\n    onceTimeout time.Duration\n    stopCh      chan struct{}\n    wg          sync.WaitGroup\n    logger      Logger\n    idleTimeout time.Duration\n    idleMu      sync.RWMutex  // Protects idleTimeout\n}\n```\n\n2. **Start/Stop lifecycle with WaitGroup:**\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) Start() {\n    gc.wg.Add(1)\n    go gc.runLoop()\n}\n\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) Stop() {\n    close(gc.stopCh)\n    gc.wg.Wait()\n}\n```\n\n3. **Ticker-based runLoop:**\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) runLoop() {\n    defer gc.wg.Done()\n    ticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)\n    defer ticker.Stop()\n    \n    gc.runOnce(context.Background())  // Immediate execution\n    \n    for {\n        select {\n        case <-gc.stopCh:\n            gc.logger.Info(\"garbage collector stopped\")\n            return\n        case <-ticker.C:\n            gc.runOnce(context.Background())\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n4. **Batch processing with error handling:**\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) runOnce(ctx context.Context) error {\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)\n    defer cancel()\n    \n    // List expired/inactive sandboxes\n    // Process each, skip NotFound, log other errors\n}\n```\n\n5. **Thread-safe configuration methods:**\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) SetIdleTimeout(timeout time.Duration) {\n    gc.idleMu.Lock()\n    defer gc.idleMu.Unlock()\n    gc.idleTimeout = timeout\n}\n\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) GetStats() GarbageCollectorStats {\n    gc.idleMu.RLock()\n    defer gc.idleMu.RUnlock()\n    return GarbageCollectorStats{...}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. Key Dependencies for AR-018\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager` | `SandboxLifecycleManager`, `Store`, `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`, `Logger` interface |\n| `pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` struct with `LastActivity` field |\n| `context` | Context for cleanup operations |\n| `sync` | `WaitGroup`, `RWMutex` for goroutine synchronization |\n| `time` | Duration, Ticker, Now for timing |\n\n---\n\n### 8. Summary of Key Findings\n\n| Aspect | Finding |\n|--------|---------|\n| Project type | Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration for AI agents |\n| Module to create | `pkg/agentd` (does not exist) |\n| AR-018 purpose | Idle Cleanup Controller for Agentd |\n| Design stage | ST-3 (design completed, ready for implementation) |\n| Reference pattern | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` |\n| Delta-spec | Most complete spec document with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios |\n| Tasks.md format | Metadata table + Phases + Dependencies + Verification + Acceptance Criteria |\n| Key constants | DefaultIdleCleanupInterval=1min, DefaultIdleTimeout=15min |\n| Deletion delegation | `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox` |\n| Store usage | `ListSessions` (Note: delta-spec says this, but workloadmanager uses `ListSandboxes`) |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28631a9bdffeHxrfJb06KOgKcw","model":{"modelID":"glm-5","providerID":"bailian-coding-plan"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775865058879,"end":1775865210429}}}}
