{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865324611,"sessionID":"ses_28631db06ffe42dcYOqg2DSQPy","part":{"id":"prt_d79d263dd001xlmIotpsChKDmq","messageID":"msg_d79d0e8f6001ANStBmn3kmJGLH","sessionID":"ses_28631db06ffe42dcYOqg2DSQPy","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-0aa13a4d3a2e415aaed877f868383b6d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md","content":"# AR-018 тАФ Agentd чй║щЧ▓ц╕ЕчРЖцОзхИ╢хЩи Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-018 тАФ Agentd чй║щЧ▓ц╕ЕчРЖцОзхИ╢хЩи |\n| Module | `pkg/agentd` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Types & Constants (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Create `pkg/agentd/doc.go` with package documentation\n  - Package name: `agentd`\n  - Description: Agentd idle cleanup controller for monitoring and cleaning idle agent runtime sessions\n  - Verification: `go doc ./pkg/agentd`\n\n- [ ] **T1.2**: Define default constants in `defaults.go`\n  - `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval = 1 * time.Minute`\n  - `DefaultIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/defaults.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/agentd`\n\n- [ ] **T1.3**: Define `IdleCleanupStats` struct for stats retrieval\n  - Fields: `Interval time.Duration`, `IdleTimeout time.Duration`, `LastCleanupTime time.Time`\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/agentd`\n\n### Phase 2: IdleCleanupController Struct & Constructor (ST-2)\n\n- [ ] **T2.1**: Define `IdleCleanupController` struct with all required fields\n  - `store Store` тАФ for session state lookup\n  - `lifecycleManager *SandboxLifecycleManager` тАФ for sandbox deletion delegation\n  - `interval time.Duration` тАФ for cleanup check interval\n  - `idleTimeout time.Duration` тАФ for idle threshold\n  - `stopCh chan struct{}` тАФ for graceful shutdown signal\n  - `wg sync.WaitGroup` тАФ for goroutine synchronization\n  - `logger Logger` тАФ for structured logging\n  - `idleMu sync.RWMutex` тАФ protects `idleTimeout` for thread-safe access\n  - `lastCleanupTime time.Time` тАФ tracks last cleanup cycle\n  - `lastCleanupMu sync.RWMutex` тАФ protects `lastCleanupTime`\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/agentd`\n\n- [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `NewIdleCleanupController` constructor\n  - Signature: `NewIdleCleanupController(store Store, lifecycleManager *SandboxLifecycleManager, interval, idleTimeout time.Duration, logger Logger) *IdleCleanupController`\n  - Apply defaults: if `interval == 0`, use `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval`\n  - Apply defaults: if `idleTimeout == 0`, use `DefaultIdleTimeout`\n  - Initialize `stopCh := make(chan struct{})`\n  - Validate non-nil store, lifecycleManager, logger\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestNewIdleCleanupController -v`\n\n### Phase 3: Lifecycle Methods (ST-3)\n\n- [ ] **T3.1**: Implement `Start()` method\n  - Call `ctrl.wg.Add(1)`\n  - Launch `go ctrl.runLoop()`\n  - Non-blocking, returns immediately\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.2**: Implement `Stop()` method\n  - Call `close(ctrl.stopCh)` to signal shutdown\n  - Call `ctrl.wg.Wait()` to block until goroutine completes\n  - Returns only after goroutine exits\n  - Safe to call multiple times (idempotent via sync.Once or nil check)\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `runLoop()` background ticker loop\n  - Run in separate goroutine (started by `Start()`)\n  - Execute `ctrl.runOnce(context.Background())` immediately on start\n  - Create `ticker := time.NewTicker(ctrl.interval)`\n  - Loop on `select { <-stopCh, <-ticker.C }`\n  - On `stopCh`: log `\"idle cleanup controller stopped\"` and return\n  - On `ticker.C`: call `ctrl.runOnce(context.Background())`\n  - Defer `ctrl.wg.Done()` and `ticker.Stop()`\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n\n### Phase 4: Core Cleanup Logic (ST-4)\n\n- [ ] **T4.1**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` тАФ session listing\n  - Call `ctrl.store.ListSessions(ctx)` to get all active sessions\n  - Log error if list fails: `\"failed to list sessions\"`\n  - Return error if list fails\n  - Iterate all sessions for idle check\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_ListSessions -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.2**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` тАФ idle status check\n  - For each session, check `time.Now().Sub(session.LastActivity)`\n  - Skip session if `LastActivity.IsZero() == true` (no activity recorded)\n  - Mark session as idle if `duration > ctrl.getIdleTimeout()`\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_IdleSession -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.3**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` тАФ cleanup execution\n  - For idle sessions: call `ctrl.lifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, session.SessionID)`\n  - Pass deletion reason as `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n  - Handle `NotFoundError`: silently ignore (already deleted), continue\n  - Handle other errors: log `\"idle cleanup failed\"` with sessionID and err, continue\n  - Log successful cleanup: `\"idle cleanup deleted session\"` with sessionID, idleDuration, reason\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_Cleanup -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` тАФ completion logging\n  - Track count of cleaned sessions\n  - Update `lastCleanupTime` to `time.Now()` after cycle completes\n  - Log: `\"idle cleanup cycle completed\"` with `cleanedCount`\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_Completion -v`\n\n### Phase 5: Runtime Configuration Methods (ST-5)\n\n- [ ] **T5.1**: Implement `SetIdleTimeout(timeout)` method\n  - Acquire `ctrl.idleMu.Lock()`\n  - Update `ctrl.idleTimeout`\n  - Release mutex\n  - Thread-safe for concurrent access\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_SetIdleTimeout -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `GetIdleTimeout()` method\n  - Acquire `ctrl.idleMu.RLock()`\n  - Return current `ctrl.idleTimeout`\n  - Release mutex\n  - Thread-safe for concurrent reads\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_GetIdleTimeout -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `GetStats()` stats retrieval method\n  - Acquire `ctrl.idleMu.RLock()` and `ctrl.lastCleanupMu.RLock()`\n  - Return `IdleCleanupStats{Interval, IdleTimeout, LastCleanupTime}`\n  - Release mutexes\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_GetStats -v`\n\n### Phase 6: Concurrent Safety (ST-6)\n\n- [ ] **T6.1**: Implement thread-safe `idleTimeout` access\n  - Add `idleMu sync.RWMutex` to `IdleCleanupController` struct\n  - Protect all reads via `getIdleTimeout()` internal method\n  - Protect all writes via `SetIdleTimeout()`\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v`\n\n- [ ] **T6.2**: Implement thread-safe `lastCleanupTime` access\n  - Add `lastCleanupMu sync.RWMutex` to `IdleCleanupController` struct\n  - Protect writes in `runOnce()` via `lastCleanupMu.Lock()`\n  - Protect reads in `GetStats()` via `lastCleanupMu.RLock()`\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v`\n\n### Phase 7: Unit Tests (ST-7)\n\n- [ ] **T7.1**: Test `NewIdleCleanupController` constructor\n  - Test: constructor returns valid instance\n  - Test: custom interval and timeout are set correctly\n  - Test: default values applied when parameters are zero\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestNewIdleCleanupController -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.2**: Test `Start()` and `Stop()` lifecycle\n  - Test: `Start()` launches goroutine\n  - Test: `Stop()` completes without hanging\n  - Test: goroutine exits cleanly\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.3**: Test `runOnce()` idle session detection\n  - Test: idle session (LastActivity > idleTimeout ago) is cleaned\n  - Test: active session (LastActivity < idleTimeout ago) remains\n  - Test: session with zero LastActivity is skipped\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_IdleSession -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.4**: Test `runOnce()` error handling\n  - Test: all sessions processed even if some cleanups fail\n  - Test: NotFound errors silently ignored\n  - Test: other errors logged but don't stop cycle\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_ContinueOnError -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.5**: Test `SetIdleTimeout()` and `GetIdleTimeout()`\n  - Test: `SetIdleTimeout()` updates threshold correctly\n  - Test: `GetIdleTimeout()` returns updated value\n  - Test: `GetStats()` reflects updated timeout\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_SetIdleTimeout -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.6**: Test concurrent access safety\n  - Test: no race conditions on `SetIdleTimeout()` concurrent access\n  - Test: no race conditions on `GetStats()` concurrent access\n  - Test: no race conditions during `runOnce()` with config changes\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v`\n\n### Phase 8: Integration & Validation (ST-8)\n\n- [ ] **T8.1**: Verify Store interface integration\n  - `store.ListSessions(ctx)` returns `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n  - Sessions include `SessionID` and `LastActivity` fields\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StoreIntegration -v`\n\n- [ ] **T8.2**: Verify SandboxLifecycleManager integration\n  - `lifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` handles K8s sandbox CR and store cleanup\n  - Deletion reason is `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_LifecycleIntegration -v`\n\n- [ ] **T8.3**: All unit tests pass with coverage\n  - `go test ./pkg/agentd -v` passes all tests\n  - Coverage: >80% for `idle_cleanup.go`\n  - No race conditions: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race`\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -func=coverage.out`\n\n- [ ] **T8.4**: Lint and build verification\n  - `go vet ./pkg/agentd` passes with zero issues\n  - `golangci-lint run ./pkg/agentd/...` passes\n  - `go build ./pkg/agentd` succeeds\n  - File: `pkg/agentd/`\n  - Verification: `go vet ./pkg/agentd && golangci-lint run ./pkg/agentd/... && go build ./pkg/agentd`\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\nT1.1 тЖТ T1.2 тЖТ T1.3\n         тЖУ\n       T2.1 тЖТ T2.2\n              тЖУ\n       T3.1 тЖТ T3.2 тЖТ T3.3\n              тЖУ\n       T4.1 тЖТ T4.2 тЖТ T4.3 тЖТ T4.4\n              тЖУ\n       T5.1 тЖТ T5.2 тЖТ T5.3\n              тЖУ\n       T6.1 тЖТ T6.2\n              тЖУ\n       T7.1 тЖТ T7.2 тЖТ T7.3 тЖТ T7.4 тЖТ T7.5 тЖТ T7.6\n              тЖУ\n       T8.1 тЖТ T8.2 тЖТ T8.3 тЖТ T8.4\n```\n\n---\n\n## Verification Commands\n\n| Task | Verification Command |\n|------|----------------------|\n| All tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -v` |\n| Constructor tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestNewIdleCleanupController -v` |\n| Lifecycle tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v` |\n| Cleanup tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce -v` |\n| Config tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_SetIdleTimeout -v` |\n| Concurrent safety | `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v` |\n| Test coverage | `go test ./pkg/agentd -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -func=coverage.out \\| grep idle_cleanup` |\n| Build verification | `go build ./pkg/agentd` |\n| Lint check | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/agentd/...` |\n| Vet check | `go vet ./pkg/agentd` |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `IdleCleanupController` struct defined with all required fields\n- [ ] `NewIdleCleanupController` constructor with default fallbacks\n- [ ] `Start()` launches background goroutine\n- [ ] `Stop()` signals shutdown and waits for completion\n- [ ] `runLoop()` uses ticker for periodic execution\n- [ ] `runOnce()` checks session idle status via `LastActivity`\n- [ ] Sessions with zero `LastActivity` skipped\n- [ ] Idle sessions trigger `DeleteSandbox` delegation\n- [ ] NotFound errors silently ignored\n- [ ] Deletion errors logged but don't stop cycle\n- [ ] `SetIdleTimeout()` runtime configuration supported\n- [ ] `GetIdleTimeout()` returns current timeout\n- [ ] `GetStats()` returns current configuration and last cleanup time\n- [ ] Default constants defined: `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval=1m`, `DefaultIdleTimeout=15m`\n- [ ] Store `ListSessions()` method used for session lookup\n- [ ] `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox()` used for cleanup\n- [ ] `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` logged for observability\n- [ ] Unit tests cover idle/active/zero scenarios\n- [ ] Unit tests cover Start/Stop lifecycle\n- [ ] Package structure follows agentcube conventions\n- [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n- [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Lines Changed | Description |\n|------|--------|---------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/agentd/doc.go` | Create | ~10 | Package documentation for agentd module |\n| `pkg/agentd/defaults.go` | Create | ~15 | `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval`, `DefaultIdleTimeout` constants |\n| `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` | Create | ~150 | `IdleCleanupController`, `NewIdleCleanupController`, `Start`, `Stop`, `runLoop`, `runOnce`, `SetIdleTimeout`, `GetIdleTimeout`, `GetStats`, `getIdleTimeout`, `IdleCleanupStats` |\n| `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` | Create | ~350 | Comprehensive unit tests (6 test groups, ~15 test cases) |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n- **Reference implementation**: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` provides similar pattern\n- **Thread-safe implementation**: Use `sync.RWMutex` for `idleTimeout` and `lastCleanupTime` fields\n- **Graceful degradation**: Cleanup continues processing even if individual deletions fail\n- **Immediate execution**: First cleanup runs immediately on `Start()`, then periodic via ticker\n- **Integration points**:\n  - `pkg/workloadmanager` тАФ `SandboxLifecycleManager`, `Store`, `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`, `Logger`\n  - `pkg/common/types` тАФ `SandboxInfo` struct with `LastActivity` field\n- **Key differences from GarbageCollector**:\n  - Uses `ListSessions()` instead of `ListExpiredSandboxes()`/`ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n  - Filters idle sessions client-side based on `LastActivity` comparison\n  - No batch size limit (processes all sessions)\n  - Tracks `LastCleanupTime` for observability\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Timeline\n\n| Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n|-------|-------|--------|------------|\n| Phase 1: Core Types & Constants | T1.1, T1.2, T1.3 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 2: Struct & Constructor | T2.1, T2.2 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 3: Lifecycle Methods | T3.1, T3.2, T3.3 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 4: Core Cleanup Logic | T4.1, T4.2, T4.3, T4.4 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 5: Runtime Config | T5.1, T5.2, T5.3 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 6: Concurrent Safety | T6.1, T6.2 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 7: Unit Tests | T7.1, T7.2, T7.3, T7.4, T7.5, T7.6 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 8: Integration & Validation | T8.1, T8.2, T8.3, T8.4 | Pending | 0% |\n\n**Total Progress: 0% Complete (0/24 tasks)**"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":37,"character":14},"end":{"line":37,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field WriteTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":13},"end":{"line":38,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field IdleTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":39,"character":17},"end":{"line":39,"character":17}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.g